{
  "texts": [
    "2D Memristor Passive CBAThe integration of memristive devices can be effectively achieved through the implementation of a crossbar array, as depicted in Fig. 4b.",
    "In this configuration, each memristor is positioned at the intersection of a WL and a BL, with the information regarding weights stored in the form of electric resistance within each individual memristor.",
    "To update these weights, a voltage pulse is selectively applied between a chosen bit line and word line, thereby initiating the program/erase process.",
    "The utilization of such a crossbar array offers several advantages, including a compact footprint that facilitates high-density integration.",
    "Furthermore, owing to its straightforward structure and ease of fabrication, it has been widely employed as the predominant architecture for memristor crossbar arrays in various studies [34,38,55,71,73,76,90,96,107]."
  ]
}